        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(line): register credential secret targets",
        "body": "## Summary\n- Register LINE channel credentials in the channel secret contract so `channels.line.channelAccessToken`, `channels.line.channelSecret`, and their account-scoped equivalents participate in audit/configure/apply surfaces.\n- Resolve LINE credential SecretRefs for enabled default and named accounts, while leaving disabled account refs unresolved with inactive-surface warnings.\n- Add coverage proving the core secret target registry discovers bundled LINE credential paths from the channel contract, and sync the generated SecretRef docs matrix.\n\n## Verification\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/secrets/target-registry.docs.test.ts extensions/line/src/secret-contract.test.ts src/secrets/target-registry.test.ts`\n- `corepack pnpm exec oxfmt --check --threads=1 extensions/line/secret-contract-api.ts extensions/line/src/secret-contract.test.ts src/secrets/target-registry.test.ts src/secrets/target-registry.docs.test.ts`\n- `git diff --check`\n\n## Real behavior proof\nBehavior addressed: LINE channel credentials are now part of the SecretRef/audit target registry instead of being absent from the channel secret contract.\nReal environment tested: local macOS source checkout on branch `fix/line-secret-contract`; real CLI path exercised with a temporary `OPENCLAW_CONFIG_PATH` containing dummy LINE credential fields.\nExact steps or command run after this patch: created a temporary `openclaw.json` with dummy `channels.line.channelAccessToken`, `channels.line.channelSecret`, and `channels.line.accounts.work.*` credentials, then ran `OPENCLAW_HOME=<tmp>/home OPENCLAW_CONFIG_PATH=<tmp>/openclaw.json node scripts/run-node.mjs secrets audit --json` and extracted the non-secret result fields.\nEvidence after fix:\n```json\n{\n  \"status\": \"findings\",\n  \"summary\": {\n    \"plaintextCount\": 4,\n    \"unresolvedRefCount\": 0,\n    \"shadowedRefCount\": 0,\n    \"legacyResidueCount\": 0\n  },\n  \"findings\": [\n    {\n      \"code\": \"PLAINTEXT_FOUND\",\n      \"message\": \"channels.line.accounts.work.channelAccessToken is stored as plaintext.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"code\": \"PLAINTEXT_FOUND\",\n      \"message\": \"channels.line.accounts.work.channelSecret is stored as plaintext.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"code\": \"PLAINTEXT_FOUND\",\n      \"message\": \"channels.line.channelAccessToken is stored as plaintext.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"code\": \"PLAINTEXT_FOUND\",\n      \"message\": \"channels.line.channelSecret is stored as plaintext.\"\n    }\n  ]\n}\n```\nObserved result after fix: `openclaw secrets audit --json` reports the LINE default-account and named-account credential fields as plaintext findings; the targeted tests also show SecretRefs resolve for enabled LINE accounts and remain unresolved with inactive warnings for disabled accounts.\nWhat was not tested: full repository test suite and a long-running gateway start/reload scenario.\n\nRefs #11829.\n",
